news.title: South Delhi civic body rejects proposal to hike property tax rates
news.para: ​The Standing Committee Chairman of the South Delhi Municipal Corporation (SDMC) BK Oberoi also rejected a proposal in the civic body's budget for 2022-23 to increase taxes on residential and commercial properties, the statement said.

news.title: HomeLane eyes Rs 1,500-crore IPO by mid-2022
news.para: Bank of America, Axis Capital and ICICI Securities have been hired to run the HomeLane IPO. They said 25-30% stake will be offered in the proposed IPO.

news.title: Homebuyers to get compensation for delays in possession of apartment
news.para: Possession that is offered by a builder over an incomplete unit will have no bearing in arriving at compensation, the consumer court said, noting that 'it is inconceivable that a person will not like to take physical possession of his Unit after having made the entire payment.'

news.title: Circle rates go up: Pay more for land or home in Gurugram
news.para: Circle rates are minimum government-defined prices at which the sale or transfer of a plot, built-up house, apartment, commercial property or land take place.

news.title: Shriram Properties' sales bookings up slightly at Rs 415 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: During the first nine months of this fiscal, the total sales bookings crossed the Rs 1,000-crore mark, reflecting a growth of 60 per cent year-on-year.

news.title: Shanghai Pudong Development Bank to issue bonds for property buys
news.para: Shanghai Pudong Development Bank Co plans to raise 5 billion yuan ($790 million) by selling three-year bonds through China's interbank market, it said in a filing on Monday. The funds would be used to finance real estate project acquisitions in the form of lending, it said.

news.title: Shimao Group creditors approve ABS payment extension: Source
news.para: Shimao held online meetings with creditors in two ABS on Monday, to vote on payment extension proposals, Reuters reported last week.

news.title: Himachal Pradesh coming out with GIS-based development plan for Shimla
news.para: Chairing a meeting of the town and country planning department to review the final draft of Shimla development plan, he said the plan is being prepared after 40 years and this is an historical development.

news.title: MPIDC applies for 9,000 acre to develop industrial area
news.para: The corporation has identified government land at potential locations along with the Delhi-Mumbai Expressway and has applied for transfer to the industry department from respective district administrations.

news.title: Embassy Group lease out 4.63 lakh sq ft to Allianz Companies in Trivandrum
news.para: The 3 million sq. ft. special economic zone (SEZ) office space is being jointly developed by Taurus Investment Holdings India and Embassy Group in Taurus Downtown Trivandrum.

news.title: Hyderabad: Residents move NGT over stone and mining units
news.para: P Indira Reddy, an organic farmer and resident of Amberpet village in Abdullapurmet mandal, and Akiti Nikhil Kumar Reddy of Chinna Ravirala in Abdullapurmet filed a petition with the NGT.

news.title: Labour crunch in Jamshedpur as most construction workers stay away
news.para: Builder Rohit Sharma said not a single worker has turned up at any of his construction sites since January 14.

news.title: Chandigarh administration adviser seeks report on land pooling policy
news.para: Recently, the UT administration asked the Indian Institute of Human Settlements (IIHS) to submit a revised draft policy on village development, regularisation of illegal structures and extension of “Lal Dora.”

news.title: To protect buyers, Jaipur development body will list illegal flats on website
news.para: The civic body will mention the list of approved projects in every zone. Moreover, it will display a list of illegal and sealed apartments on its website.

news.title: Submit proposal to reduce building misuse penalties: MHA tells Chandigarh admin
news.para: The response comes after UT's request of giving powers to the UT administrator. Last year, the ministry had asked the UT to submit afresh proposal and the UT had sought some clarifications.
